f those digits is 3 + 3 = 6 which is even, so the answer is 1.\n\n \nConstraints:\n\n1 <= nums.length <= 100\n1 <= nums[i] <= 100\n\n\n\n### Format: You will use the following starter code to write the solution to the problem and enclose your code within delimiters.\n```python\nclass Solution:\n    def sumOfDigits(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:\n        \n```\n\n### Answer: (use the provided format with backticks)\n", "response": "```python\nfrom typing import List\n\nclass Solution:\n    def sumOfDigits(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:\n        # Find the minimum element in the list\n        min_num = min(nums)\n        \n        # Calculate the sum of the digits of the minimum element\n        digit_sum = sum(int(digit) for digit in str(min_num))\n        \n        # Return 0 if the sum is odd, otherwise return 1\n        return 0 if digit_sum % 2 == 1 else 1\n```\n\nThis solution first finds the minimum element in the given list `nums`. It then converts this minimum element to a string to iterate over each digit, converts each digit back to an integer, and calculates the sum of these digits. Finally, it checks if the sum is odd or even and returns `0` for odd and `1` for even, as specified in the problem statement.", "estimated_date": 1560038400000}